OL,6,FThe general secretary of the FDA, a
OL,7,Funion for civil servants, has said
OL,8,Fthat meaningful reform "must put
OL,9,Fsubstance before headlines" and any
OL,10,Fannouncement that "points the finger"
OL,11,Fat public staff "only reinforces the
OL,12,Fsense that the government lacks of a
OL,13,Fcredible long-term plan".
OL,15,FDave Penman said: "If the government
OL,16,Fis serious about transforming public
OL,17,Fservices they must set out what the
OL,18,Fsubstance of reform looks like, not
OL,19,Fjust the retreading of failed ideas
OL,20,Fand narratives."
